## <a id='overview'></a> Overview

Pivotal Application Service (PAS) for Windows enables operators to provision, operate, and manage Windows cells on <%= vars.product_name  %>.

After operators install the PAS for Windows tile on the Ops Manager Installation Dashboard, developers can push .NET applications to Windows cells using the 
[Cloud Foundry Command Line Interface](https://docs.pivotal.io/platform/2-7/cf-cli/) (cf CLI).

For the PAS for Windows release notes, see the 
[PAS for Windows v<%= product_info['local_product_version'].to_s %> Release Notes](https://docs.pivotal.io/platform/<%= product_info['local_product_version'].to_s.sub('.','-') %>/pcf-release-notes/windows-rn.html) topic.

## <a id='reqs'></a> Requirements

To install the PAS for Windows tile, you must have the following:

* Ops Manager v2.7 and PAS v2.7 deployed to vSphere, Amazon Web Services (AWS), Google Cloud Platform (GCP), or Azure.  

* A Windows stemcell, which you can obtain by following the directions in [Downloading or Creating Windows Stemcells](./stemcells.html).  

The minimum resource requirements for each Windows cell are as follows:

* Disk size: 64&nbsp;GB (100&nbsp;GB recommended)

* Memory: 16&nbsp;GB

* CPUs: 4


